      "type": "multiple_choice",
      "question": "Why should hyperparameters not be chosen based on test-set performance?",
      "stem_format": "plain_text",
      "choices_format": "plain_text",
      "choices": [
        "It leaks evaluation information and gives an unreliable estimate of generalization.",
        "It prevents the algorithm from using a validation set later.",
        "It always makes k equal to 1, regardless of the data.",
        "It makes the model unable to store the training images."
      ],
      "answer_index": 0,
      "explanation": "The test set is meant to be a final unbiased check. Using it to select settings turns it into part of the tuning process, so the reported performance no longer reflects truly unseen data.",
