      "question": "Why is nearest neighbor on raw pixel values a weak practical image classifier?",
      "stem_format": "plain_text",
      "choices_format": "plain_text",
      "choices": [
        "Semantically different images can still be close under pixel-level distances.",
        "Pixel distances are impossible to compute for RGB images.",
